@1=~As you travel alongside Ulfbrand and his forces toward a towering corridor behind the high walls of the Great Foundry, you cannot help but wonder about two things. First, just how large a force did the Fated Factor manage to assemble on such short notice? You can only hope the Doomguard are prepared at the site of their ambush. The other thing that keeps drawing your attention is the notion of... consequence..~
@2=~Your choices put this in motion. Could the Doomguard have hidden away? Could Ulfbrand have gotten distracted? Could Rowan Darkwood have changed his mind about this? Could Haer'Dalis and his troop have sneaked out of the City of Doors unseen, to some quaint Prime Material world to have more adventures of their own? All of these peaceful options are now off the table. This is going to get violent, and you helped it reach this point.~
@3=~How does it make you feel?~
@5=~Very good. The carnage will be wonderful.~
@6=~Very good. Utter a silent prayer to your new patron, the Lady of the Dead. The loss of life that is about to unravel is no cause for tears. The many bodies will likely be reused in their silent and perfect obedience of undead servitude. It is the ultimate goal of all life.~
@7=~Very good. Utter a silent prayer to your new patron, the Lady of the Dead. The loss of life that is about to unravel is no cause for tears. The many bodies will likely be reused in their silent and perfect obedience of undead servitude. It is the ultimate goal of all life. The philosophy of the Dustmen, so close to your heart, is so clearly in line with what the multiverse is heading towards.~
@8=~Good. Only the strong will survive. This is the way of the planes. There is no reason to feel regret about it.~
@9=~Good. The city will bathe in blood this day. The Fated want to take everyone's belongings. The Doomguard embrace decay and destruction. Neither are worth your tears.~
@10=~You do not know. You can only hope that this was the right path to take.~
@11=~You are unsure. You have to believe that your choices are right. If this path is the only way to stop the slow undoing of the planes, it must be the right one, even if it seems terrible.~
@12=~Bad. Whatever secrets about your past await you in the deepest reaches of the Hells, they cannot be worth all the lives that will be lost today. Still, it is too late to stop this conflict.~
@13=~It does not make you feel anything.~
@15=~As the large squadron makes its way foundrywards, many locals hide indoors, shops close, and windows shutter to snuff the line of sight of curious children. Meanwhile, some creatures in the city have the opposite reaction. Many fiends stay outside and smile, sensing inevitable carnage. The legion of the Fated is made up of many men and women from Sigil, but also a significant number of seasoned warriors loyal to Ulfbrand, who traveled here from Ysgard. These streets rarely see such a display of power.~
@16=~There is a moment of tension as a patrol of Mercykillers appears, escorting a strange, amorphous creature, with an apparent victim still visible inside of it, partially digested. There are six of them, a force intimidating enough to scare most into submission, but their authority dwindles in the face of the continuous stream of silent, motivated creatures. They share some discreet whispers, perhaps discussing if it is even worth trying to do anything about this...~
@18=~Ignore all this. Focus on the task at hand. You are here to lead Ulfbrand into a trap. Do not stray from the path now.~
@19=~Spit toward the Mercykillers. It is a rare opportunity to do so without them being able to do anything about it.~
@20=~Discreetly signal the Mercykillers to try and stop this somehow. ~
@21=~Discreetly signal the Mercykillers to try and stop this somehow. ~
@23=~The Mercykillers clearly get your message, while the large half-giant walking next to you, busy dictating the rhythm of this march, seems entirely oblivious to your exchange. Nevertheless, they just turn around, pretending not to see you or any of the legion. Their apathy is an ironic harbinger of the unavoidability of what is to come.~
@24=~*Mmmmm.*~
@26=~Ignore all this. Focus on the task at hand. You are here to lead Ulfbrand into a trap. Do not stray from the path now.~
@27=~Spit toward the Mercykillers. It is a rare opportunity to do so without them being able to do anything about it.~
@29=~"Don't look at them, little one. They won't join our ranks. Their kind only preys on the weak and helpless. The Doomguard will put up a fight," Ulfbrand comments, apparently aware of your non-verbal attempt but misjudging your intentions. The Mercykillers leave your sight. You do not know if they got your message.~
@31=~Ignore all this. Focus on the task at hand. You are here to lead Ulfbrand into a trap. Do not stray from the path now.~
@33=~The smoke from the Great Foundry gets ever closer. While the journey, filled with thoughts, seems to be very long, it becomes clear that the event itself is at hand. Ulfbrand starts barking some preliminary orders toward his lieutenants. Eventually, he turns to you.~
@35=~Pretend you are too focused on some inner mantra.~
@36=~Turn to Ulfbrand. Listen to what he has to say.~
@38=~Ulfbrand tries to get your attention twice, then moves on to shouting something to the spellslingers in the back. He is clearly not very fond of them, though he understands he is no longer in his comfortable dead magic zone.~
@39=~You also have an opportunity for some communication. You do not have much time, though. You may only exchange a few glances.~
@41=~You are alone in this. Your temporary allies lie in wait where the smoke bellows. It's almost time.~
@42=~Try to make eye contact with your companion.~
@43=~Try to make eye contact with one of your companions.~
@44=~There is no time. You are almost there.~
@46=~Ulfbrand studies you for a moment.~
@47=~"Little one, you seem to have quite a swing. Do not get mixed up with the other warriors. You're better suited to picking off stronger foes. Keep your eyes open."~
@48=~"Little one. You're a spellslinger, aren't you? Join them when the fighting starts. Stay out of the thick of it."~
@49=~"Little one, you seem agile. You're one of those rogue types, aren't you? Keep to the flanks and see if you can pick off any stragglers. Do not throw yourself into the fray."~
@50=~"Little one, I'm not quite sure what your best qualities are, but stay out my bersërkers' way, just in case."~
@51=~You also have an opportunity for some communication. You do not have much time, though. You may only exchange a few glances.~
@53=~You are alone in this. Your temporary allies lie in wait where the smoke bellows. It is almost time.~
@54=~Try to make eye contact with your companion.~
@55=~Try to make eye contact with one of your companions.~
@56=~There is no time. You are almost there.~
@58=~Who would you like to signal?~
@60=~Look at Dak'kon. A fighter whose strategy and calm may turn the tide of battle.~
@61=~Look at Morte. He has been by your side from the start. He is fast and can get into places no one else can. He could be crucial in surprise attacks.~
@62=~Look at Annah. She has spent her life in the shadows, and they are her domain. She could slip behind enemy lines and strike at foes when they are at their most vulnerable.~
@63=~Look at Grace. A beacon of hope in the dead of night. She will likely save many lives today. You only need to keep her sheltered from the heat of battle.~
@64=~Look at Nordom. From a good position on higher ground, he could really thin the ranks of your opponents.~
@65=~Look at Vhailor. He could focus the enemies' attention on himself and withstand a lot, giving more vulnerable allies time to act.~
@66=~Look at Ignus. He is going to wreak havoc, likely as much among enemies as among allies.~
@67=~There is no time. You are almost there.~
@69=~The faithful githzerai stays silent. He just nods, fully aware of what you expect him to do.~
@70=~You look away from Dak'kon and glance to see how far the Foundry is.~
@72=~You are alone in this. Your temporary allies lie in wait where the smoke bellows. It is almost time.~
@73=~Look at Dak'kon. A fighter whose strategy and calm may turn the tide of battle.~
@74=~Look at Morte. He has been by your side from the start. He is fast and can get into places no one else can. He could be crucial in surprise attacks.~
